
// This Hyperlambda code sends a message using Twilio's API. It constructs the message body from a result node, sets the recipient and sender using arguments, and uses Twilio account credentials for authentication. The slots [body], [to], [from], [twilio_account_id], and [twilio_account_sid] are crucial for specifying the message content, recipient, sender, and authentication details respectively.
signal:magic.twilio.send-message
   body:x:@signal/@signal/*/result
   to:x:@.arguments/*/from
   from:x:@.arguments/*/to
   twilio_account_id:x:@.twilio_account_id
   twilio_account_sid:x:@.twilio_account_sid
